title: The (d,p) and (d,t) reactions on 38Ar and 40Ar

x4freetext: The (d,p) and (d,t) reactions on 38Ar and 40Ar

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.114, p.392 (1968)

x4freetext: The primary deuteron beam entered the gas
volume through a nickel foil of 1.7 mg/cm2. The
reaction products were allowed to leave the gas volume
through havar windows of 3.5mg/cm2 and could be
detected at reaction angles between 10. and 140. ang.
The reaction products were
identified by dE/dx-E counter telescopes using surface
barrier counters and Li drifted silicon detectors.

x4freetext: The measurement of reactions on 38Ar was particularly
difficult due to the fact that the natural isotopic
mixture of argon contains only 0.063 % of 38Ar. Thus
as little as 7 cm3 NTP of 38Ar enriched to 97.5% was
at the disposal. A special gas target has been
designed in order to handle this comparatively small
quantity of gas.The total volume of the gas target
was about 10 cm3.
